    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Blotters bearing advertisements. Some, advertising mainly school supplies, were issued to school children in France from the late 19th century up until the 1960s. In mid-20th century,  Esquire Magazine was advertised by blotters featuring movie star pin-up drawings and photos. Customized advertising blotters are still produced today.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049971/National Museum of American History [online] (1999-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vloeiblokken waarop advertenties zijn afgebeeld. Sommige, voornamelijk met advertenties voor schoolgerei, werden van het midden van de 19de eeuw tot in de jaren 60 van de 20ste eeuw uitgereikt aan schoolkinderen in Frankrijk. Medio 20ste eeuw adverteerde Esquire Magazine op vloeiblokken met tekeningen en foto’s van filmsterren. Speciaal ontworpen reclamevloeiblokken worden nog steeds gemaakt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>附有廣告的記事簿。自十九世紀末起，直到西元1960年代，有些廣告記事簿專門發給學童，主要以廣告文具用品為主，發行於法國地區。二十世紀中葉時，《君子雜誌(Esquire Magazine)》用記事簿作廣告，以電影明星畫報與照片為特色。現今訂製的廣告記事簿仍持續印製。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
